		<title>Q1 2018 mapping project: Petrol stations</title>
		<link>https://www.mappa-mercia.org/2018/01/q1-2018-mapping-project-petrol-stations.html</link>
					<comments>https://www.mappa-mercia.org/2018/01/q1-2018-mapping-project-petrol-stations.html#comments</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[RobJN]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 09 Jan 2018 22:01:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Participate]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mappa-mercia.org/?p=1517</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Following a lengthy discussion on the talk-gb mailing list and several false starts, Ilya recently imported UK Shell petrol station data into OpenStreetMap.To confirm the quality of the third party data a brand new community validation tool was developed. Use &#8230; <a href="https://www.mappa-mercia.org/2018/01/q1-2018-mapping-project-petrol-stations.html">Continued</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-1518 aligncenter" src="https://www.mappa-mercia.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/petrol_station.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="337" srcset="https://www.mappa-mercia.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/petrol_station.jpg 640w, https://www.mappa-mercia.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/petrol_station-300x158.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></p>
<p>Following a lengthy discussion on the talk-gb mailing list and several false starts, Ilya <a href="https://lists.openstreetmap.org/pipermail/talk-gb/2017-December/021011.html">recently imported</a> UK Shell petrol station data into OpenStreetMap.To confirm the quality of the third party data a brand new <a href="https://lists.openstreetmap.org/pipermail/talk-gb/2017-December/020972.html">community validation tool</a> was developed. Use of this tool highlighted a lot of inconsistency in the way we map &#8211; as such let&#8217;s make petrol stations the quarterly mapping project for Q1 2018.</p>
<p>According to <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/312331/number-of-petrol-stations-in-the-united-kingdom-uk/">Statistica</a> there are some 8450 petrol stations in the UK. Compare this to OpenStreetMap, where <a href="http://taginfo.openstreetmap.org.uk/tags/amenity=fuel">TagInfo shows</a> that we have mapped 7200. Not bad &#8211; just 1250 more to go! Let&#8217;s see if we can get to the magic 8450 by the end of the quarterly project (or show that the real number is indeed different). This also gives us a great opportunity to review the existing data, updating old tags to reflect on-the-ground change and converting petrol stations mapped as points (nodes) to ones mapped as areas (closed ways).</p>
<p><em>Image: CC-By-Sa 2.0 <a title="View profile" href="http://www.geograph.org.uk/profile/11162" rel="cc:attributionURL dct:creator">Betty Longbottom</a></em></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
